<subSubSection id="4E3DA5E90685C171D227806838C83059" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="263E617082A28A916402EEAEE67781EA" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D8D52F3427F3A5E8E87B348B0EC361DD" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName id="F84687CBDFADB8391B72609CC0AACD70" authority="Dahlbom, 1854" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1854" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga aureomaculata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aureomaculata">
<emphasis id="65CB016028AF1AA63D82CC560CD27B2F" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Holopyga aureomaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Abeille is recognized to be the male of 
<taxonomicName id="C3FDFE41DF6E292D9CAC5C848B93938B" authority="Dahlbom, 1854" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1854" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga ignicollis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ignicollis">
<emphasis id="C2F633F7492BCAD23763C932897B6575" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Holopyga ignicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dahlbom. This is a dubious identification, which can perhaps be referenced to 
<taxonomicName id="5AE00FC7B77CC72484A4E088C8E5115F" authority="Dahlbom, 1854" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1854" baseAuthorityName="Foerster" baseAuthorityYear="1853" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga chrysonota" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysonota">
<emphasis id="63483FABC8473E835BC3024277B47B30" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Holopyga chrysonota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In 
<bibRefCitation id="A1510592D7F05FE3B9B37ABBB94EDF84" author="Kimsey, LS" journalOrPublisher="Oxford University Press, New York" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" refId="B56" refString="Kimsey, LS, Bohart, RM, 1991. The Chrysidid Wasps of the World. Oxford University Press, New York" title="The Chrysidid Wasps of the World." year="1991">Kimsey and Bohart (1991</bibRefCitation>
: 230) 
<taxonomicName id="80F59FB17E4870FC97915B23C047871A" authority="Dahlbom, 1854" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1854" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga ignicollis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ignicollis">
<emphasis id="1FF76BC3FFE40C0265E7056991EB8775" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Holopyga ignicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="249C1770F7209B24766428576E98228F" authority="Dahlbom, 1854" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1854" baseAuthorityName="Foerster" baseAuthorityYear="1853" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga chrysonota" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysonota">
<emphasis id="030042C8CA8DD312CB18632BF37C8E21" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Holopyga chrysonota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the two species are clearly distinct.
</paragraph>
